The paper deals with formal models of knowledge and belief, which are central topics in logic and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the relationship between qualitative and quantitative modeling, which is relevant to multi-agent systems and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
